condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, A1 | Description :The Republic of Armenia shall maintain, at all times during Projectimplementation, the CEP as the Project Implementation Unit (PIU) within MOES, with a mandate, staffing and other resourcessatisfactoryto the Bank (“PIU” or “CEP”) | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, C2 | Description :The Republic of Armenia shall ensure that the Micro-project Sub-grantsand CIF Sub-project Sub-grants are made to Beneficiaries in accordance with eligibility criteria and procedures set forth in theOperational Manual and in Section I.C. of the Loan Agreement and the Financing Agreement. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, C3 | Description :Except as the Association may otherwise agree in writing, no proposedMicro-project and/or Sub-project shall be eligible for financing unless the Recipient has determined the proposed Micro-projectand/or Sub-project satisfies the eligibility criteria set out in the Loan Agreement, Financing Agreement and the OperationalManual. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, D1 | Description :The Republic of Armenia shall ensure that the Project is carried outinaccordance with the Environmental Management Framework (EMF) and site-specific Environmental Management Plans (EMPs). | Frequency:CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, D2 | Description :Except as the Bank may otherwise agree in writing, no proposedMicro-project or Sub-project shall be eligible for financing unless the Recipient has determined, on the basis of an appraisal,carried out in accordance with guidelines acceptable to the Bank, that the respective Micro-project or Sub-project satisfies theeligibility criteria for safeguards specified in the Project Operational Manual. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section II, A1 | Description :The Republic of Armenia shall monitor and evaluate the progress oftheProject and prepare Project Reports in accordance with the provisions of Section 4.08 of the General Conditions and on the basisofthe indicators acceptable to the Bank. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section II, B1 | Description :The Republic of Armenia shall maintain or cause to be maintained afinancial management system in accordance with the provisions ofSection 4.09 of the General Conditions. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

title.narrative: 4. Share of grants established under the CIF achieving at least 80 per cent of their proposed objectives.
3. Increased number of high schools equipped with education resources provided by the project.
Five to six year old children enrolled in preschools supported by the project. (Indicator to be measured at the aggregate level as well as separate by gender)
Number of community-based pre-schools supported by the project.
Number of higher education institutions benefiting from the CIF’s component
Number of administrative staff trained in the use of the integrated Education Management Information Systems (Indicator to be measured at the aggregate level as well as separate by gender).
2. Increased number of high schools targeted by the project which meet Armenia’s construction & safety standards.
Number of partnerships between public and private institutions established under the CIF
Number of classrooms rehabilitated in high schools resulting from project interventions
Number of subjects whose standards and syllabi have been revised and endorsed by the Government
Utility of the learning assessment system
Improved student attendance in high schools targeted by the project (Indicator to be measured at the aggregate level as well as separate by gender).

baseline.value: Baseline collected for treatment & control high schools (collected in school year 2013-2014).

target.value: Student attendance in high schools targeted by the project is improved according to the dynamic data available at schools andtarget group’s opinions.

actual.value: The data on student attendance is being collected in schools targeted by the project.

title.narrative: 1. Improved school readiness among those entering first grade in participating communities (Indicator to be measured at the aggregate level as well as separate by gender).

baseline.value: Baseline collected in September 2014 for treatment & control group for the communities selected in the first round. For thecommunities to be selected in the second round, the baseline will be collected in September 2015 and furnished in July 2016.

target.value: EDI scores are higher in treatment group as compared to control group and this difference is statistically significant

actual.value: Indicator achieved. EDI scores have increased in treatment group on average by 18 percent between the beginning and end of anacademic year as opposed to 4 percent in control group; Source: Baker Tilly Report (2016).Based on the Baker Tilly Report (2019)the average difference between the beginning and an end of an academic year for all tested domains was 35.33% for the target group,and 24.96% for the control group. This difference is statistically significant.

title.narrative: System for the maintenance of hardware and software of Armenian schools designed and in operation

target.value: System fully operational and expanded nationwide

actual.value: The development of the NACET datacenter is completed along with the rehabilitation of the NaCET building.

title.narrative: Education Management Information System for general and higher education integrated and in operation.

target.value: Integrated system fully operational and expanded nationwide

actual.value: The works on the integration of EMIS and EMIS systems have been completed, the corresponding software designed, which also includeschanges and improvements in the reporting system. EMIS is fully operational.
